articles.title: Israel kills 53 in Gaza, flattens more towers as toll from famine rises
articles.description: Israeli forces have killed 53 Palestinians across the Gaza Strip and levelled 16 buildings in Gaza City, including three residential towers, as they ramp up an offensive to seize the northern urban centre and displace its population [3]. At least 35 of the victims on Sunday were killed in Gaza City, according to medics [3].

articles.title: Suspect in assassination of Charlie Kirk arrested on suspicion of capital murder, weapons and obstruction offenses
articles.description: A suspect has been arrested in connection with the assassination of Charlie Kirk and is facing charges including capital murder, weapons offenses, and obstruction [2].

articles.title: Netanyahu and Rubio stick to established Israeli-US narrative on Gaza war
articles.description: Netanyahu reiterates Israel takes 'full responsibility' for Qatar attack; Rubio says Hamas must 'cease to exist' [4]. United States Secretary of State Marco Rubio and Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu have held further talks cementing the countries' close alliance, as the Arab-Islamic summit of regional leaders gathered in Doha to denounce the unprecedented attack on Qatar last week [4].
